<h2>Related Training Opportunities</h2>

<p>This course is part of a developing curriculum for training of NCI clinical and postdoctoral fellows. Each Fall, a course in "<a alt="Translational Research in Clinical Oncology" href="https://ccr.cancer.gov/training/trainee-resources/courses-workshops/traco" target="_blank" title="Translational Research in Clinical Oncology">Translational Research in Clinical Oncology</a>"(TRACO) hosted by <a alt="Dr. Terry Moody" href="mailto:moodyt@mail.nih.gov" title="Dr. Terry Moody">Dr. Terry Moody</a> is offered primarily for NIH postdoctoral fellows.</p>

<p>Also "Demystifying Medicine for PhDs" has 2 hours of lecture each week from January-May and the course is hosted by <a alt="Dr. Irvin M. Arias" href="mailto:ariasi@mail.nih.gov" title="Dr. Irvin M. Arias">Dr. Irvin M. Arias</a>. For additional opportunities for postdoctoral training at NIH, view <a alt="https://www.training.nih.gov/" href="https://www.training.nih.gov/" target="_blank" title="https://www.training.nih.gov/">https://www.training.nih.gov/</a></p>

